@page "/security"

<PageTitle>Security - Smart Maintenance</PageTitle>

<div class="security-page">
    <div class="page-header">
        <h1>üîí Security & Compliance</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Your data security is our top priority</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="security-intro">
            <p>At Smart Maintenance Management System, we implement industry-leading security practices and technologies to protect your data. Our comprehensive security framework ensures confidentiality, integrity, and availability across our entire platform.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="security-section">
            <h2>üõ°Ô∏è Infrastructure Security</h2>
            <h3>Data Encryption</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Encryption in Transit:</strong> All data transmitted between clients and servers is encrypted using TLS 1.3 with 256-bit AES encryption</li>
                <li><strong>Encryption at Rest:</strong> Database storage uses AES-256 encryption for sensitive data fields</li>
                <li><strong>Key Management:</strong> Encryption keys are rotated regularly and stored in secure hardware security modules (HSMs)</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Secure Hosting</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Cloud infrastructure hosted on enterprise-grade data centers with SOC 2 Type II certification</li>
                <li>Redundant systems across multiple availability zones for 99.9% uptime SLA</li>
                <li>DDoS protection and web application firewall (WAF) for threat mitigation</li>
                <li>Regular infrastructure security audits and penetration testing</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="security-section">
            <h2>üîê Authentication & Access Control</h2>
            <h3>Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)</h3>
            <p>We strongly recommend enabling MFA for all accounts:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Time-based One-Time Passwords (TOTP) via authenticator apps</li>
                <li>SMS verification codes</li>
                <li>Email verification links</li>
                <li>Hardware security keys (FIDO2/WebAuthn)</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Granular permission system with least-privilege principle</li>
                <li>Customizable roles: Admin, Manager, Technician, Client</li>
                <li>Activity logging for all permission changes</li>
                <li>Automated session timeout and re-authentication for sensitive operations</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Password Security</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Bcrypt hashing with high computational cost (12+ rounds)</li>
                <li>Password strength requirements enforced</li>
                <li>Protection against brute force attacks with rate limiting</li>
                <li>Secure password reset flow with time-limited tokens</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="security-section">
            <h2>üè¢ Multi-Tenant Data Isolation</h2>
            <h3>Tenant Separation</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Logical Isolation:</strong> Each organization's data is logically separated in the database with tenant identifiers</li>
                <li><strong>Query-Level Enforcement:</strong> All database queries automatically filter by tenant context</li>
                <li><strong>API-Level Validation:</strong> JWT tokens include tenant information validated on every request</li>
                <li><strong>Cross-Tenant Protection:</strong> Middleware prevents unauthorized access to other tenants' data</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Tenant Security</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Each tenant has isolated user accounts and authentication</li>
                <li>Tenant-specific encryption keys for sensitive data</li>
                <li>Separate backup and disaster recovery per tenant</li>
                <li>Audit logs track all cross-tenant access attempts</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="security-section">
            <h2>üìä Application Security</h2>
            <h3>Secure Development Practices</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Security-first development lifecycle with threat modeling</li>
                <li>Code reviews focused on security vulnerabilities</li>
                <li>Automated security scanning (SAST/DAST) in CI/CD pipeline</li>
                <li>Dependency vulnerability scanning and automatic updates</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>OWASP Top 10 Protection</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>SQL Injection:</strong> Parameterized queries and ORM usage</li>
                <li><strong>XSS Prevention:</strong> Input sanitization and Content Security Policy (CSP)</li>
                <li><strong>CSRF Protection:</strong> Anti-CSRF tokens on all state-changing operations</li>
                <li><strong>Authentication Flaws:</strong> Secure session management and JWT best practices</li>
                <li><strong>Sensitive Data Exposure:</strong> Encryption, secure headers, and minimal data exposure</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="security-section">
            <h2>üîç Monitoring & Incident Response</h2>
            <h3>24/7 Security Monitoring</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Real-time intrusion detection and prevention systems (IDS/IPS)</li>
                <li>Automated anomaly detection using machine learning</li>
                <li>Security Information and Event Management (SIEM) for centralized logging</li>
                <li>Continuous vulnerability scanning and remediation</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Incident Response Plan</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Dedicated security incident response team (SIRT)</li>
                <li>Documented procedures for detection, containment, and recovery</li>
                <li>Communication protocols for affected customers within 72 hours</li>
                <li>Post-incident analysis and preventive measures</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Audit Logging</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Comprehensive audit trails for all user actions</li>
                <li>Immutable logs stored for compliance (1+ year retention)</li>
                <li>Admin activity tracking and alerting</li>
                <li>Login attempts, permission changes, and data access logged</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="security-section">
            <h2>‚úÖ Compliance & Certifications</h2>
            <h3>Industry Standards</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>SOC 2 Type II:</strong> Annual audits for security, availability, and confidentiality</li>
                <li><strong>ISO 27001:</strong> Information security management system certification</li>
                <li><strong>GDPR Compliant:</strong> Full compliance with EU data protection regulations</li>
                <li><strong>CCPA Compliant:</strong> California Consumer Privacy Act adherence</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Data Residency</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Data stored in geographically distributed data centers</li>
                <li>Option to specify data residency region for compliance</li>
                <li>Cross-border data transfer protections (Standard Contractual Clauses)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="security-section">
            <h2>üîÑ Backup & Disaster Recovery</h2>
            <h3>Data Backup</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Automated daily backups with 30-day retention</li>
                <li>Encrypted backup storage in geographically separate locations</li>
                <li>Point-in-time recovery capability</li>
                <li>Regular backup restoration testing</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Business Continuity</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Disaster recovery plan with 4-hour Recovery Time Objective (RTO)</li>
                <li>1-hour Recovery Point Objective (RPO) for data loss minimization</li>
                <li>Failover systems across multiple regions</li>
                <li>Annual disaster recovery drills and testing</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="security-section">
            <h2>üë• Vendor & Third-Party Security</h2>
            <h3>Vendor Management</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Security assessments for all third-party vendors</li>
                <li>Due diligence reviews and ongoing monitoring</li>
                <li>Contractual security requirements and SLAs</li>
                <li>Limited data sharing with vendors (need-to-know basis)</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Third-Party Integrations</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>OAuth 2.0 / OpenID Connect for secure integrations</li>
                <li>API security with rate limiting and authentication</li>
                <li>Regular security reviews of integrated services</li>
                <li>Granular permissions for third-party app access</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="security-section">
            <h2>üì± Security Best Practices for Users</h2>
            <h3>Account Security</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Enable multi-factor authentication (MFA) immediately</li>
                <li>Use strong, unique passwords (12+ characters, mixed case, numbers, symbols)</li>
                <li>Never share your credentials or session tokens</li>
                <li>Log out from shared or public devices</li>
                <li>Regularly review your account activity logs</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Data Protection</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Be cautious of phishing emails claiming to be from SMMS</li>
                <li>Verify the URL before entering credentials (smartmaintenance.com)</li>
                <li>Report suspicious activity immediately to security@smartmaintenance.com</li>
                <li>Keep your browser and operating system updated</li>
                <li>Use antivirus software and keep it current</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="security-section">
            <h2>üö® Reporting Security Vulnerabilities</h2>
            <h3>Responsible Disclosure</h3>
            <p>We appreciate the security research community's efforts to keep our platform secure. If you discover a security vulnerability, please:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Report it to <strong>security@smartmaintenance.com</strong> with detailed information</li>
                <li>Allow us reasonable time to investigate and remediate (typically 90 days)</li>
                <li>Avoid accessing or modifying user data beyond proof-of-concept</li>
                <li>Do not perform destructive testing (DoS, data deletion, etc.)</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Bug Bounty Program</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>We offer rewards for qualifying security vulnerabilities</li>
                <li>Severity-based compensation (Critical: $500-$5000, High: $200-$1000)</li>
                <li>Public acknowledgment on our security hall of fame (optional)</li>
                <li>Coordinated disclosure process with credit to researchers</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="security-updates">
            <h2>üì¢ Security Updates</h2>
            <p>We publish security advisories and updates regularly. Subscribe to our security mailing list to receive notifications about:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Security patches and updates</li>
                <li>Maintenance windows affecting security systems</li>
                <li>New security features and enhancements</li>
                <li>Best practice recommendations</li>
            </ul>
